    <text id="B1076T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson reports on the number of rations issued to blacks during previous
                months.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Office 4th Division, 9th
                    Sub-District, Virginia.
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr> John A.
                            McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">Sub Asst.
                        Comr</abbr><lb/>Winchester</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-08-31"><abbr expan="August">Aug</abbr> 31st 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Captain</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>In compliance with Circular No 16 C.S. <abbr expan="Headquarters">HdQrs</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr> State of <abbr
                        expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr> I have the honor to report that no Rations have
                    been issued to Colored paupers in this Division since June 1867. During that
                    month I issued (as per report) as follows to --</p>

                <p><hi rend="underline">Adults</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">5</hi> Males, <hi rend="underline">12</hi> Females Total
                        <hi rend="underline">17</hi> - <hi rend="underline">Children</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">5</hi> Males <hi rend="underline">9</hi> Females, Total <hi
                        rend="underline">14</hi>. <hi rend="underline">Aggregate 31</hi>, <hi
                        rend="underline">Aggregate May Report 40</hi>. <hi rend="underline">Total
                        Rations <abbr expan="issued">iss<hi rend="super">d</hi></abbr> 616</hi>.</p>

                <p>The <unclear>favorable</unclear> result of crops here and the evident ability of
                    the County to support the poor within its limits led me to suspend further
                    issues.</p>

                <p>I addressed a communication to the County Court now in session in Augusta County
                    and transmit herewith copy of reply. In Highland <abbr expan="county">Co.</abbr>
                    there are few Freedmen, these nearly all belong to that county and the
                    authorities are fully able to provide for them.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="Your obedient servant">Yr obt servt</abbr>
                    </salute>
                    <signed><hi rend="underline">Thos P. Jackson</hi><lb/>Agent</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
